name: Warung Dinda
address: Jl. Raya Senganan, Jatiluwih, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1:
I thought when we were going to Bedugul, there will be no food as good as ubud or south bali, BUT I WAS WRONG, the food in TABANAN is one of the best food taste we ever try,
One of hidden gem, if you want to go to Bedugul from Jatiluwih, I STRONGLY Recommended this food for you to try,
WHY? i tell u why:
1. The food is suprisingly TASTE EXECELENT
2. The plate and other cutleries is CLEAN
3. The food is worth the price
4. As always, Bali is strongly known for their hospitality

review 2: A humble restaurant in Tabanan. The food was nice, the price is totally worth it. Will surely comeback for another Nasi Campur when I visit Tabanan next time.
review 3: Didn't look for this place but we only stopped as we needed something to eat and didn't regret it. For traditional food, the quality of the cuisine is real good. Tasty. I wish I could find something like this new where I live in the city, but sadly nope. The pork they're using are superbly fresh as I did see them cutting the meat at the back and it seems like they just don't stop cooking
review 4: Decent local restaurant at local prices.
